hub.com/licenses/unlicense","node_id":"MDc6TGljZW5zZTE1"},"allow_forking":true,"is_template":false,"web_commit_signoff_required":false,"topics":["cli","command-line","command-line-tool","gitignore","grep","recursively-search","regex","ripgrep","rust","search"],"visibility":"public","forks":2304,"open_issues":88,"watchers":57154,"default_branch":"master","permissions":{"admin":false,"maintain":false,"push":false,"triage":false,"pull":true}},"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/BurntSushi/ripgrep/pulls/3162","html_url":"https://github.com/BurntSushi/ripgrep/pull/3162","diff_url":"https://github.com/BurntSushi/ripgrep/pull/3162.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/BurntSushi/ripgrep/pull/3162.patch","merged_at":"2025-10-05T14:05:27Z"},"body":"Closes #3158 \r\n\r\nThis replicates the behavior of `walkdir`, where passing `.min_depth(1)`, `.min_depth(0)` or no `min_depth` will have the same behavior.\r\n\r\nPassing `min_depth(Some(2)` to the builder to a directory that looks like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\n.\r\n├── a\r\n│   ├── b\r\n│   │   ├── c\r\n│   │   │   └── foo\r\n│   │   └── foo\r\n│   └── foo\r\n└── foo\r\n```\r\n\r\nWill returns something like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\n[\"a/b\", \"a/b/c\", \"a/b/c/foo\", \"a/b/foo\", \"a/foo\"]\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhile passing a `min_depth` of `0`, `1` or `None`: \r\n\r\n```\r\n[\"a\", \"a/b\", \"a/b/c\", \"foo\", \"a/foo\", \"a/b/foo\", \"a/b/c/foo\"]\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf the user passes a `max_depth` < `min_depth` then we set `max_depth = min_depth` as `walkdir` does. ","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/BurntSushi/ripgrep/issues/3162/reactions","total_count":2,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":2,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/BurntSushi/ripgrep/issues/3162/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}},"event":"cross-referenced"},{"id":20101670443,"node_id":"REFE_lADOAzJbyc7NjZhKzwAAAASuJyYr","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/BurntSushi/ripgr